# Feed Scheduler & Refresh Discipline

Consult `../kiji-doc/docs/tauri/feed-scheduler-refresh.md` before changing background refresh, feed fetch timeouts, `feedRefreshActivity`, OPML boosts, or article-list header widgets.

## Required invariants

1. **Timeout:** `FEED_FETCH_TIMEOUT_MS` is 5s everywhere (renderer + Rust default). Do not lengthen without Electron parity review.
2. **Refresh indicator:** `feedRefreshActivity.track()` wraps `fetchFeedNetworkWithCache` only — never parse/store. Scheduler cycles call `beginQueuedFeeds` on the prioritized run plan and release each feed when HTTP settles so sidebar text counts down (not stuck at concurrency cap).
3. **Scheduler pool:** One ephemeral `createTaskPool` per cycle; concurrency 3–8 via `getConcurrency()`. No unbounded parallel refresh or persistent cross-cycle queues.
4. **Tick coalescing:** Overlapping native ticks → `pendingCycleTick`; run one deferred cycle after the current one finishes.
5. **OPML boost:** `boostMany` starts a cycle when idle; if a cycle is running, set `pendingCycleTick` instead of nesting cycles.
6. **Article-list widgets:** `ArticleListWidgets` stays inside `.article-list-title-section`, absolutely positioned `top: 12px; right: 16px` on the panel.

## Before finishing

